00:54:07,293 --> 00:54:12,496
use all their cards all the time. Thank you. Over here.

993
00:54:13,335 --> 00:54:19,018
Sometimes when you make newer iterations of, like, say, Pokemon or Magic,

994
00:54:19,218 --> 00:54:23,481
like, there were sometimes when you made a new card that just was better than a previous card.

995
00:54:23,941 --> 00:54:25,442
How do you counter that later on?

996
00:54:25,462 --> 00:54:29,384
Like, if you did it, if you did it intentionally, if it was accident, but later on,

997
00:54:29,444 --> 00:54:32,866
you know, sometimes, like, people will have cards that are just not really worth anything

998
00:54:32,886 --> 00:54:34,027
because they have the better version.

999
00:54:34,547 --> 00:54:36,208
So how do you counter that later on?

1000
00:54:37,028 --> 00:54:37,168
Well...

1001
00:54:38,065 --> 00:54:39,806
That's gone back and forth over the years.

1002
00:54:39,846 --> 00:54:45,088
We had a rule at one time that no card was supposed to be strictly better than any other card in the whole set.

1003
00:54:47,109 --> 00:54:50,510
It was a good rule of thumb, but it didn't really work out.

1004
00:54:50,610 --> 00:54:57,172
So eventually we just started making cards better or worse because of where we wanted the end goal to be.

1005
00:54:57,512 --> 00:55:05,435
You will be forced into obsoleting certain cards when you make tens of thousands of different magic cards.

1006
00:55:06,903 --> 00:55:11,567
You'll be forced to do that. And the same thing if you're designing a computer game, same exact sort of thing.

1007
00:55:12,427 --> 00:55:17,292
If you have enough objects, some are just going to be strictly better than others, and you can't help it.

1008
00:55:18,232 --> 00:55:23,137
Would it be better to try to plan ahead of time to make sure that it doesn't happen, or does it really matter?

1009
00:55:23,637 --> 00:55:31,684
You know, is it better to just like, you know, to make sure, like, try to put, you know, a lot of effort into trying to not do that, or just let it happen?

1010
00:55:32,693 --> 00:55:37,975
Um, I think you should plan for it to not happen, but then when it does, don't be too

1011
00:55:38,035 --> 00:55:41,356
afraid and too resistant if you're actually going to end up in a better space.

1012
00:55:41,836 --> 00:55:43,917
Yes, certainly the ideal is that that doesn't happen.

1013
00:55:43,937 --> 00:55:45,538
I just, I don't think that's realistic.

1014
00:55:46,198 --> 00:55:50,019
Uh, so I, I do think sometimes you'll have to just say, yeah, you know, lightning bolt

1015
00:55:50,059 --> 00:55:51,500
should cost whatever.

1016
00:55:52,100 --> 00:55:54,101
R for two damage instead of R for three damage.

1017
00:55:54,501 --> 00:55:55,081
That kind of thing.

1018
00:55:55,221 --> 00:55:57,322
It just, yeah, you'll be forced into that.

1019
00:55:58,062 --> 00:55:58,242
Yes.

