00:58:10,043 --> 00:58:11,743
for people to be able to successfully do that

1068
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:12,683
if it's a hard job.

1069
00:58:13,703 --> 00:58:16,064
And I'm not saying that there aren't people

1070
00:58:16,084 --> 00:58:18,965
that could do it, but if you really want to provide

1071
00:58:19,005 --> 00:58:20,985
a lot of value from the complexity of the system,

1072
00:58:21,325 --> 00:58:22,965
that's almost impossible.

1073
00:58:24,105 --> 00:58:42,941
And then secondarily, when you get to the end of that campaign, you, I guess, I don't know, I would question how smart I was if I didn't lose any of the things, if I didn't lose any battles, it's very difficult for me to get feedback on how well or poorly I did.

1074
00:58:44,342 --> 00:58:48,145
I think it's more the nature of the complexity of the system makes it.

1075
00:58:49,448 --> 00:58:53,991
I definitely understand, and in fact the game that we submitted that was rejected had a lot of that in it,

1076
00:58:54,951 --> 00:59:05,437
but I think you still needed to generate the losses in order to, yeah, in order to really do the hard thinking about your deck.

1077
00:59:06,157 --> 00:59:06,438
Thank you.

